headline: Fair Isaac (FICO) Is Down 7.2% After Soft Guidance And ARR Miss What's Changed
summary: In recent days, Fair Isaac Corporation reported quarterly results with revenue broadly matching analyst expectations but issued full-year guidance that came in below consensus and included a slight miss on annual recurring revenue, pointing to a slower period for the business. An interesting wrinkle is that, despite this softer outlook compared with peers, investor interest in the company’s long-term prospects and competitive positioning appears to be intensifying. headline: Q3 Earnings Roundup: Fair Isaac Corporation (NYSE:FICO) And The Rest Of The Data & Business Process Services Segment
summary: The end of an earnings season can be a great time to discover new stocks and assess how companies are handling the current business environment. Let’s take a look at how Fair Isaac Corporation (NYSE:FICO) and the rest of the data & business process services stocks fared in Q3.
